<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1167835370688">
<term>arithmetic sequence</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167835370694">An arithmetic sequence is a sequence where the difference between consecutive terms is constant.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167835370699">
<term>common difference</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167835370704">The difference between consecutive terms in an arithmetic sequence, <m:math><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> is <emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis>, the common difference, for <emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis> greater than or equal to two.</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
